The role of absolute humidity on transmission rate of the COVID-19 outbreak

Dataset associated with the article: “The role of absolute humidity on transmission rates of the COVID-19 outbreak”. The dataset include: Epidemiological data as daily cumulative confirmed incidence data from the Johns Hopking Center for S Science and System website from January 23, 2020 to February 10, 2020; Estimation of a proxy for the reproduction number based on the cumulative incidence data for each province; Weather data as monthly values of temperature and absolute humidity data in January 2020 for each provincial capital in China from World Weather Online; Demographic data as the population density in 2014 and the latitude and longitude of each provincial capital.
17 February 2020 - Luo W, Majumder MS, Liu D, et al. The role of absolute humidity on transmission rates of the COVID-19 outbreak. medRxiv. January 2020:2020.02.12.20022467.
Article describing the analysis and methods for this dataset
